\subsection{Algebraic Functions}

Rational functions are a subset of the \textbf{algebraic functions}, functions that are expressible using \(x,\) \(y,\) and the standard arithmetic operations (addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division) in addition to exponentiation. Here are the graphs of two rational functions.\\

\noindent \figurelabel

